      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<div type="commentary" xml:lang="eng">
	  <p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:Sarma1993">Sarma and Varaprasada Rao 1993</ref>; the translation is by Andrew Ollett.</p>
	</div>
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  siddhaṃ raño
	  <persName key="pers:VpŚrīSātakarṇi">
	    vāsiṭhīputasa siri sāta<supplied reason="lost">kaṇisa</supplied>
	  </persName>
	  <lb n="2"/>
	  pavajitena 
	  <persName key="pers:Nāgabuddhī">nāgabudhi<supplied reason="lost">nā</supplied></persName>
	  antevāsinīya bhikuṇīyā
	  <lb n="3"/>
	  yakhiyāya<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation">
	<p>
	Success! (During the rule of) 
	<persName key="pers:VpŚrīSātakarṇi">Vāsiṣṭhīputra
	Śrī Sāta(karṇi)</persName>, a nun internee named 
	<persName key="pers:Nāgabuddhī">Nāgabuddhī</persName>
	caused ... a yakṣa ...
	</p>
      </div>
